The paper deals with the design and synthesis of correct distributed protocols, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of extended state machines and model checking suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of an SMT solver, which is a tool commonly used in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The focus on correctness and synthesis of unknown functions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with symmetry constraints, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of control systems and optimization (cs.SY).
